[Black "Ruy Lopez,  Steinitz Defense #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 d6
{ The classical Steinitz Defense did not stand the test of time and already for a long time it has been considered passive and unpromising, though some strong players still try it occasionally. }
4. d4 Bd7
{ The most popular continuation according to Mega Database does not deserve to be one. It is hard to imagine what Black could possibly hope for other than a good chance that White wouldn't now the best reaction. I intend to deal with this hope. }
5. Bxc6
{ Important nuance: after  5.Nc3  exd4  6.Nxd4  Nf6  7.Bxc6  Black can recapture with a Pawn but now doesn't have that option. }
5... Bxc6 6. Nc3 exd4 7. Nxd4 Nf6 8. Qe2
{ Black will not be able to develop his dark-squared Bishop on the long diagonal now. }
8... Be7 9. Be3 O-O 10. f3
{ We want to castle long and then proceed with a typical kingside g4, h4 etc. but without Black's typical counterplay. }
