[Result "*"]

1. e4 d6 2. d4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7
{ The main point of the Modern Defense is to delay Ng8-f6. Whether it's useful is another story. }
4. Be3
{ The exclamation mark is for the integrity of our repertoire - in many lines Modern will transpose directly to Pirc which makes absorbing these lines easier. }
4... a6
{ Usually, this is the point of delaying Ng8-f6. Black wants to go b7-b5 but avoid e4-e5. }
5. Qd2
{ Of course there are other moves too but it seemed so simple for White and Wesley So did it too, I mean he can't be wrong, can he? }
5... b5 6. O-O-O Bb7
{ Black might want to provoke f2-f3 and then try to delay Ng8-f6. } 7. f3 Nd7
8. h4 h5
{ This is not so different from  8...h6  , at least we react in the same way. }
9. Nh3 Rc8 { 9...c5  runs into the same problem -  10.dxc5! } 10. Ng5
{ We didn't have this after 8...h6. } 10... c5 11. e5 cxd4
{ The other point of White's 11.e5 can be seen in the following line:  11...dxe5  12.dxe5  Bxe5  13.Nxf7!  Kxf7  14.Qxd7  . }
12. e6 fxe6 13. Bxd4 e5 { The e6-Pawn might run away... } 14. Bf2
{ But the square will not - Black has to cover it. White has a gigantic compensation for the Pawn. We can continue with Bc1-d3, then try Rh1-e1 and Nc3-e4. }
