{ This move is wrong by definition as the Bishop blocks the 'd' Pawn - something you shouldn't be doing in general. However in some e4 e5 lines it is actually justified if it connects with one of the two reasonable ideas:  a@@EndBracket@@ Re8, Bf8 and d7-d5;   b@@EndBracket@@ Ne7, Ng6, c6, Bc7 and d5.   In both cases Black saves time by skipping d7-d6. We'll keep that in mind but for now let's refute this nonsense. }
