{ 8...bxc6 was weak but at least Black could say that he was trying to keep more pieces on board. What can he say now? White has a better pawn structure plus look at the Black's Bishop! }
10. f4 O-O 11. Qf3 Qd7
{ Black is hoping to swap the Queens but we can easily prevent that and Black's Queen is misplaced on d7. }
12. h3 Qe6 { Improving the position of the Queen. } 13. Be3
{ We don't really need to do anything special, just develop our pieces. If Black doesn't do anything then we can continue with 14. Rae1. }
13... d5 14. e5 Nd7 15. Bd4
{ Now f4-f5 is a threat. If Black stops it with  15...g6  then we can further improve with  16.Rae1  .   15...Qf5  can be calmly answered with  16.Rac1  . White is much better. }
