14... Qd5 15. b3
{ By placing the Pawns on the light squares White successfully implements the strategy of playing against the opponent's Bishop as it will have no targets now. At the same time, White's Bishop is getting some new hideouts.   Of course, we choose b2 over f2 as black is missing the f-Pawn @@StartBracket@@The reader should Notice that the light-squared Bishop won't able to find a good place on the board. }
