19. Rxb6 Nc6 20. Rfb1
{ White has a slow but deadly plan of pushing the a-pawn as far as possible. }
20... Nd8 { The Pawn advance is stopped but now other ideas arise. } 21. Ra6
{ the Rook can't be taken } 21... Nc6 { Draw? } 22. Rbb6
{ No, thank you! White's Rooks are really cheeky! } 22... bxa6
{ We should always consider what to do if they take down one of ours. Especially when there are no good alternatives for the opponent  22...Kd8  23.Rxc6  bxc6  24.Qa5+!  wins the Rook back -  24...Qc7  25.Ra8+  Kd7  26.Qxc7+  Kxc7  27.Rxe8  and Black's position is hopeless. }
23. Rxc6+ Kd8 { 23...Kb8  would be even simpler:  24.Rxa6  Qb7  25.Qa5+-  . }
24. Ng5 { Black's King will go for a walk. } 24... Ke7 25. Rxa6
{ In view of Ra6-a7 and Qd5-f7 Black's King has to keep moving. } 25... Kf6 26.
Ne4+ Kg6 { There was no coming back as after  26...Ke7  d6 would fall. } 27.
Ra3 { In open positions the Rooks can be incredibly mobile! } 27... h6
{ 27...Qf5  would easily lose to  28.Rf3  . } 28. Rg3+ Kh7 29. Qd3
{ Black cannot stop 30. Nf6 and  29...Kg8  makes no difference! } *

