11... a6 12. Re1
{ White is preparing Nc3-d5. The truth is this position can be handled in many ways.  12.a5  was possible, as well as  12.Be2  with idea of playing Nf3-h2-g4. In this regard this has been my subjective choice. }
12... h6 13. Nd5 Bf7 14. Nd2
{ Or  14.c3  . We are basically doing the same as if Black had played a7-a5. }
14... O-O 15. c3 Kh8 16. b4
{ But this is different. White's position is slightly better as he might prepare further advance on the queenside while it is much more difficult for Black to build counterplay on the Kingside. }
