[Round "?"]
[White "5. Ruy Lopez Cozio Defense (3...Nge7)"]
[Black "Cozio Defense 3...a6 #7"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6
{ Besides the obvious idea - winning the Bishop - Black's last move is useful for another reason - sooner or later Black might want to go b7-b5, making the b7-square available for his light-squared Bishop. }
4. Ba4 Nge7 5. Nc3
{ 5.d4  exd4  6.Nxd4  is weaker now - White has already committed to Bb5-a4 which helps Black. We could go 6.O-O!? but I want to give Black a chance to use a bad line. }
5... g6 { Now we are more or less forced to push the Pawn to d4. } 6. d4 exd4
7. Nd5 { The normal 7. Nxd4 was also possible but I like this more. } 7... Bg7
8. Bg5 h6 { This pin can't be tolerated. } 9. Bf6
{ Once again we manage to swap Black's dark-squared Bishop - no fun for Black! }
9... Bxf6 10. Nxf6+ Kf8 11. Bb3
{ A novelty. Immediate  11.Nxd4  runs into  11...Nf5!  and things are not clear at all. }
11... Kg7 12. Nxd4
{ The point - Black can't capture the Knight -  12...Kxf6??  13.Qf3+  wins. }
12... Ng8 13. Nxg8 Rxg8 14. Ne2 d6 15. O-O
{ Without the dark-squared Bishop Black's position will always be a bit unpleasant. If he now goes  15...Re8  then  16.Nc3  followed by 17. f4 should be nice. }
