{ If Black manages to play d7-d6 and c6-c5 without our interference he might actually get a decent game. Therefore we are going to interfere. }
12. c3 { Speeding up the events. } 12... c5 13. cxb4
{ In Dominguez - Nakamura, Opera euro rapid, 2020,  13.Nb3  was played. It is also what Swiercz recommends in The Modernized Ruy Lopez A Complete Repertoire for White. After careful investigation, I wasn't sure if White was fighting for the advantage. }
13... cxd4 { The Pawn sacrifice doesn't look convincing to me. } 14. bxa5
{ 14...Qxa5?  15.Bf4  would already be clearly better for White. } 14... O-O
15. Nd2
{ Actually some other moves were possible too but this one looks simple and logical. }
15... d5
{ Once again  15...Qxa5  wouldn't be a good idea -  16.Nc4  and Black is in trouble. }
16. b4
{ Black doesn't have enough compensation for the Pawn. He will most likely play  16...d3  to which we will reply with  17.Rb1  followed by 18. Bb2. It might not be easy to move the b Pawn but once it moves it is going to be hard to stop it. }
