{ The move is logical - he can now meet  10.e5  with  10...Bb7  . However there is a more straightforward continuation: }
10. c3 { Black's position should collapse after this. } 10... dxc3 11. bxc3
Qxc3 12. Rc1
{ Everything went wrong about the opening for Black - all pieces, except for the Queen are still in their starting positions. Black's position is already lost -  12...Qb4  can be simply met with  13.Rb1  followed by 14. e5 - Black can't stop Nd2-e4 as our Rook controls b7.    13...Qa3 or 14...Qa5 - 14. Nc4 is even worse... Finally if Black gives up on c5 - we take it and then c7 will be the next one. The numerous weak dark squares in Black's camp will be easily occupied by our forces. }
