9... a6
{ Black wants to push our Bishop away from this diagonal but he might also fianchetto his own Bishop. }
10. Ba4 d3 11. Re1 Nf4
{ It is a risky strategy as Black is behind in development but it doesn't mean we can ignore it! }
12. g3 Ne6 13. Nbd2
{ 13.Qxd3?!  Nc5  would surely suit Black. White's Knight is heading to e4. }
13... Nc5 { Stopping Nd2-e4 but also attacking the Bishop. } 14. Bxc6 dxc6 15.
b4
{ Without this resource the opening would be a success for Black but now our Knight will reach its dream outpost. }
15... Ne6 16. Ne4
{ Black is still solid but from a practical point of view this is a fantastic position for White. The d3 Pawn is virtually lost and there are plenty of squares for White's pieces while Black struggles to get any activity. }
