1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Bc5 4. c3 f5
{ One of the ideas that are always scary to face over the board but once you check them at home they are not scary at all. }
5. d4 { Usually the simplest means are the best. } 5... exd4
{ Now White gets a huge advantage: } 6. e5
{ Black's kingside is terribly weak now, he is also solidly underdeveloped. }
6... dxc3 7. Nxc3 Nge7 { The Knight has to be satisfied with e7 square... } 8.
O-O O-O 9. Nd5
{ Despite being a pawn up, Black's position is just horrible. We can bring our Bishop to c4 but apart from that we have some nice ideas like Bc1-g5 or b2-b4. }
