1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Bc5 4. c3 Nge7
{ There have been a few top level games in recent years but I am not sure why. }
5. O-O
{ In my opinion this is more accurate than immediate  5.d4  exd4  6.cxd4  Bb4+  . }
5... d5 { As attractive as it looks, it doesn't pose any problems for White. }
6. Nxe5 O-O
{ In case you wondered what happens after  6...dxe4  -  7.Nxf7!  Kxf7  8.Qh5+  happens :-@@EndBracket@@. }
7. Bxc6 bxc6
{ 7...Nxc6  doesn't change anything -  8.Nxc6  bxc6  9.d4  and White is a clean Pawn up. }
8. d4 Bd6 9. exd5 cxd5 10. Bf4
{ Black has no compensation for the Pawn. The simple Nb1-d2 and Rf1-e1 is our follow-up. }
