6. Bxc6 { Rare case yet it is justified - development first! } 6... Nxc6 7. d4
exd4 8. cxd4 Ba7
{ I think Black is missing at least a tempo to make this setup looks interesting. }
9. d5 Ne7 10. d6
{ Breaking Black's pawn structure and also making the light-squared Bishop even weaker... }
10... cxd6 11. Nc3
{ We will simply win the d6 Pawn back with Bc1-f4xd6 leaving Black with an inferior pawn structure and chaotically placed pieces }
