[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "7. Ruy Lopez Classical Defense (3...Bc5)"]
[Black "Classical Defense 4...Nf6 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Bc5 4. c3 Nf6 { The main continuation. } 5. d4
{ With the Knight on e7 it was best to castle first. Now however,  5.O-O  allows  5...O-O  6.d4  Bb6!  and I am not sure if White has any advantage at all. The difference will become clear once we see 5...Bb6 line. }
5... Bb6 6. Nxe5
{ This is much stronger than  6.dxe5?!  Nxe4  attacking the Pawn on f2. } 6...
Nxe5
{ Basically the only try for Black  6...O-O  7.Bd3   or  6...Qe7  7.Bxc6  is all you need to know. }
7. dxe5 Nxe4 { Now f2 is under attack. } 8. Qg4
{ Now imagine both side have already castled - you see the difference, right? }
8... Bxf2+ 9. Ke2 Qh4
{ There was nothing else but also - It doesn't look so clear yet. } 10. Qxg7
Rf8 11. Bh6 { Black only has one defense. } 11... Bc5 12. Nd2
{ It is important no to panic about  12...Qf2+  . } 12... Qf2+ 13. Kd1
{ We need to be precise -  13.Kd3?!  Nxd2  14.Bxd2  Qf5+  would be fine for Black. }
13... Nxd2 14. Bxd2 Be3
{ Eliminating our dark-squared Bishop might seem like a good decision but Black is also eliminating his own defender. }
15. Bxe3 Qxe3 16. Rf1
{ Apart from 17. Bc4, White is threatening to open up the position with 17. e6! Black can't stop them both. }
16... Qc5 17. e6 fxe6 18. Kc2 { 19. Be2 will decide. } *

