[Black "Classical Defense 4...Nf6 #10"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Bc5 4. c3 Nf6 { The main continuation. } 5. d4
{ With the Knight on e7 it was best to castle first. Now however,  5.O-O  allows  5...O-O  6.d4  Bb6!  and I am not sure if White has any advantage at all. The difference will become clear once we see 5...Bb6 line. }
5... exd4 6. e5 Nd5 7. cxd4 Bb4+ 8. Nbd2
{ As many different lines and openings @@StartBracket@@for instance QGA @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp1pppp/8/8/2pP4/8/PP2PPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.e4  e5  4.Nf3  exd4  5.Bxc4  Bb4+  6.Nbd2!  @@EndBracket@@  - covering with Knight is considered to be more ambitious. The point is that once White castles the Bishop will just look silly on b4. }
8... d6 9. O-O O-O 10. Ne4
{ The Knight is usually the strongest in the center and this is not exception. White is threatening with  10...--  11.Bg5  so Black has to do something -  11...Bf5  12.Qe2   or  10...--  11.Bg5  dxe5  12.dxe5  Nde7  13.Qa4  look both very nice for us. }
