[Round "?"]
[White "9. Ruy Lopez Delayed Classical (3..a6 4.Ba4 Bc5)"]
[Black "Delayed Classical  8...Bxd2+ #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6
{ Besides the obvious idea - winning the Bishop - Black's last move is useful for another reason - sooner or later Black might want to go b7-b5, making the b7-square available for his light-squared Bishop. }
4. Ba4 Bc5
{ We can already smell something unusual about Black's play. Why else would he encourage us to go  5.c3  right away? The line has caught up some real attention this year so we should take it seriously. }
5. c3 Nge7
{ There it is. Black wants to get an improved version of the Cozio Defense. After  6.O-O  Ng6  7.d4  Ba7  8.Bg5  f6!  things might get really interesting. I don't think there is a need for complications here as White has an easy solution to the line. }
6. d4 { Now Black has no choice but to take on d4. } 6... exd4 7. cxd4 Bb4+
{ Otherwise we would just go 8. d5 with great advantage. } 8. Bd2 Bxd2+ 9. Qxd2
{ If we ever need a change then  9.Nbxd2  is also fine. What I like about our line is that Black can never get an interesting position. This is important - on most occasions such lines are used as surprises so it's good to have a solid response. }
9... d5 { Now  10.e5  is out of question -  10...Bg4  is just fine for Black. }
10. exd5 Qxd5
{ This is even more interesting - the move was first played in Alekhine, A - Bogoljubow, E in a famous St. Petersburg 1914 tournament. }
11. O-O
{ 11.Nc3  Qe6+  was played in the game. After  12.Qe3  @@StartBracket@@instead of 12.Kf1?! played by Alekhine@@EndBracket@@ White can still play for advantage but overall I think that our choice is better. Black can now choose what is more important for him - blocking the d5-square or avoiding doubled pawns. }
11... O-O { Now White can easily get d4-d5. } 12. Nc3 Qd6 13. d5 b5
{ This is stronger than  13...Na5  14.Bc2!  and Black can't activate the Knight -  14...Nc4?  15.Bxh7+! }
14. dxc6 { The next few moves are forced. } 14... Qxd2 15. Nxd2 bxa4 16. Nxa4
Nxc6 17. Nb3
{ The Knight won't stay on b3 for long - it's coming to c5. We can then occupy the c and d files with our Rooks. I don't know how serious this is but definitely White is slightly better as Black's weaknesses are permanent. }
