10. exd5 Nxd5
{ This brought Jordan Van Forrest a draw in his play-off rapid game against Anish Giri in Tata Steel Masters 2021. He did suffer, though. }
11. Bxc6+ { There was no reason to delay this. } 11... bxc6 12. O-O
{ This is the biggest weakness of the whole line - after @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/1pppnppp/p1n5/2b1p3/B3P3/2P2N2/PP1P1PPP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 1 6@@EndFEN@@  6.O-O  Ng6  7.d4  Ba7  Black was ready for a fight, welcoming some sharp and risky lines. Here however, there is no fun, just a Petroff-style fight for a draw. The line is simply inconsistent. }
12... O-O 13. Ne5
{ It is a very clever try - after  13.Nc3  Nxc3!  14.Qxc3  Be6  Black would put his Bishop on d5 just in time. Now it is not that simple. }
13... Re8 { Now Black is ready to meet  14.Nc3  with  14...c5! } 14. Re1
{ Defending the Knight. } 14... Be6 15. Nc3
{ Black will not be able to bring the Bishop to d5. The presence of the Rook on e8 ruin everything -  15...Nxc3  16.Qxc3  Bd5  17.Nxc6  and after  17...Bxc6  18.Qxc6  Black can't take the d4-Pawn. }
