14... a5 15. f3 a4 16. Nc5 { Otherwise this would be not clear at all. } 16...
Nxc5 17. Bxf5 Ne6 18. Bxe6 fxe6 19. Be3
{ White has a solid situation on the Queenside controlling the c-file which means he has a free hand on the Kingside - f3-f4 and g3-g4 is just a matter of time. }
