{ 19...Qh4  would be met with  20.Ba3  - anyway the back rank is covered. } 20.
b4 { We had to stop c7-c5. } 20... Qf4 21. Bd2 Qf2+ 22. Kh1
{ White is ready to go Ra1-g1 and Bd2-e1. } 22... a5 23. Bb3
{ Defending the Pawn on a2. If he advanced the a-pawn then we can simply come back to c2. Otherwise Ra1-g1 followed by Bd2-e1 is the plan. }
*

