18. cxd4 Nxd4 19. Nxd4 exd4
{ This sharp move is not fully sound but it's not easy to prove it, which makes it a good practical try. }
20. Bb2 dxe3
{ Accepting the sacrifice loses quickly but the moves are not that simple so let's see this till the end. }
21. Qh5 g6 22. Bxg6 { The Bishop cannot be touched. } 22... Qe7 23. Re1
{ The only winning move. The Rook joins the attack. } 23... Rf2
{ After  23...Bd7  White can play simple  24.h3  - Black is helpless. } 24.
Rxe3 Rxb2 25. Bxh7+
{ A final blow. The Bishop cannot be taken - after  25...Qxh7  26.Rg3+  White wins the Queen and then also the Rook on b2. }
25... Kg7 26. Rg3+ Kf8 27. Be4 { Black can't defend against all our threats. }
