19. Qd2 Nf7 { Now Black is threatening with d5-d4. } 20. Qf2
{ Anticipating the threat. } 20... Rd7 21. Rad1
{ Black is having some difficulties with finding the proper setup for his pieces. We can continue with something like Rf1-e1 and maybe in the future we will manage to execute f3-f4 and g2-g4.   21...c4  should be answered with  22.b3!  While after  21...Qc6  @@StartBracket@@preparing Nd8-e6@@EndBracket@@  we can go  22.h4!  The point is that  22...Nd8  is met with  23.Bh6  Rf7  @@StartBracket@@23...Re8 24. Qg3! and the Queen has to come back to e6@@EndBracket@@  24.f4  and we will push the Pawns to h5 and later to g4. }
