{ Preventing both d5-d4 and Qe6-b6 @@StartBracket@@Bf4-e3@@EndBracket@@. White's chance are slightly preferable as Black has keep watching out for a4xb5 and Ra1-a5. }
21... Rd7 { I feel compelled to walk you through this natural plan. } 22. axb5
axb5 23. h3
{ No, we are not preparing g2-g4, it's a bit more complicated than that. We would love to prevent d5-d4 with Qd2-d4 but there is always Nd8! followed by Nc6.   Therefore make a generally useful move waiting for  23...Rfd8  and if he does that -  24.Qd4  comes, this time effectively. }
23... d4 { Luckily for him, he can advance the Pawn first. } 24. cxd4 Rfd8 25.
Qc3 Rxd4 26. Be3
{ after the Rook's retreat we will go f3-f4 with a small edge. White controls the a-file and potentially he can even try g2-g4 in the future. Black has to sit tight and adjust only to our plans. }
