{ For a long time I had a feeling that this was one of those lines that everybody knows about but nobody talks about. Finally GM Swiercz broke the conspiracy. }
13. Nxc5 Bxc5
{ 13...Qxd1?!  14.Rxd1  Bxc5  15.Be4  willtranspose to 14...Qxd1?! } 14. Be4
Qd7
{ This is the supposed idea nobody wanted to talk about @@StartBracket@@or play, for that matter@@EndBracket@@. Why? My bet is they all hoped to meet this idea with White :-@@EndBracket@@ }
15. Bg5 { A surprising resource - White putting the development first. } 15...
cxb2 16. Rb1
{ Taking the b2 Pawn has dramatic consequences - The c file opens and Black won't be able neutralize White's attack though there are tricks. }
16... h6 17. Qc2 Bc4 { The only move that does not lose instantly. } 18. Rfd1
Qe6 19. Bf5 { The Queen is almost trapped! } 19... Nb4 20. Qd2 Qd5
{ 20...Qxf5  leads to a mate in two:  21.Qd8+  Rxd8  22.Rxd8# } 21. Qc3 Qc6
{ 21...hxg5  is objectively the best chance but after  22.Rxd5  Nxd5  23.Qxb2  White should win anyway. }
22. e6 { White has a winning attack. } 22... O-O 23. Bxh6 gxh6 24. Ne5 Bxf2+
25. Kh1
{ White still has to be careful - after  25.Kxf2?  Qc5+!  suddenly Black is winning! }
25... Qb6 26. Ng4 { There is no defense against White's threats. } *

