{ Black will have to sacrifice that Queen. } 21... Qc6 22. Rd7+ Qxd7
{ After  22...Ke8  White would calmly continue with Rb2-b1-d1. } 23. Bxd7 Kxd7
24. h4
{ Now our King is safe while the g5 square might be used by the Knight at some point. Technically we don't even have material advantage but White's initiative is simply too strong. We are threatening with Nf3-d2 but also e5-e6+ is there as well as simple Qc2-e4 and Rb2-d2+. }
