15. Bg5 { A surprising resource - White putting the development first. } 15...
h6
{ Black would be very happy to see 17. Bh4 as he can play g7-g5 at any time blocking the white Bishop. However none of this is going to happen because we won't move the Bishop. }
16. Qc2
{ A surprising resource! Even with the Pawn on c3 the c file can be used to our advantage. }
16... hxg5 17. Rad1 Nb4
{ Black is really lucky to have this one - otherwise White might be just winning! }
18. Qxc3 Bxf2+ { Another lucky shot! } 19. Kxf2 Nd5 20. Qc5 c6 21. Nxg5
{ 21.Nd4  would be great if not  21...Rh4! } 21... Rh5 22. Nf3 Qa7
{ The worst part for Black is over but White manages to maintain some pressure in the endgame. }
23. Rc1 Ne7 { Delaying Qa7xc5+ allows Black to buy some time. } 24. b3 Qxc5+
25. Rxc5 Rc8 { 25...Rd8  26.h4  is also slightly better for White. } 26. Rfc1
Kd7 27. R5c3 Bg4 28. Re3
{ The Rook will be perfectly placed on e3 - it supports the Pawn on e5 and - when needed - it can be easily regrouped via the 3rd rank. Black's position is solid but unpleasant as White is likely to create a passed Pawn on the kingside at some point. }
