{ Very nice way to activate the Rook. It can be placed on g3 - threatening with Bc1-h6 - or f3 - threatening with Bc1-g5 and preventing any counterplay involving advancing f7 Pawn @@StartBracket@@something like Nf6-d7 and f7-f5@@EndBracket@@.   Then we can develop the Knight to c3 and, if the light-squared Bishop is still there - move it to c4. This is a long-term observation but Black will eventually suffer on the queenside - he has a weak Pawn on a6 and moving it a5 badly weakens b5. }
