{ If Black can push the Bishop back to g3 then it makes a lot of sense. The problem is that he can't. }
15. Nxg5 hxg5 16. Bxg5 Kg7 17. Qf3
{ Apart from the usual pin, Black's main problem is the Knight on a5 and it's the problem that can't really be solved. }
17... Rh8 18. axb5 axb5 19. Nd2
{ Black would like to move the light-squared Bishop to c8-h3 diagonal but in order to do that he has to anticipate b2-b4 first.   However after  19...Rb8  White has simple  20.Bd3  - which is our plan anyway. }
