16. Nbd2
{ White wants to play the simple 17.Qe2. Black can solve the problem of the b-pawn with  16...b4  but this weakens the c4-square -  17.Nc4  Bc5  18.a5  and White is better.   One more useful thing - Black can't play  16...g5?  -  17.Nxg5  hxg5  18.Bxg5  followed by Qd1-f3 and Nd2-f1-g3 is too strong. Black can never go Re8-e6 because of simple Bc2-b3 @@StartBracket@@remember how I told you about the b3-square?@@EndBracket@@. }
