16... c6 { White should be better here but that task isn't obvious. } 17. Ra3
{ Black can't take  17...cxd5  as  18.Rg3  Kh7  19.e5!  dxe5  20.Rxe5  would win. }
17... Ne6 { We are forced to take the Knight. } 18. Bxe6 fxe6 19. Rg3
{ On the other hand there is no good square for the King now. } 19... Kf7
{ The lesser evil. } 20. Bxf6 Qxf6 21. Rf3 Ke7
{ Black has some compensation here so we should be careful. } 22. Rxf6 Rxf6 23.
Rf1 { We can't defend the Pawn but this had to be played anyway. } 23... Rxf2
{ or  23...Raf8  24.Nd2  . } 24. Rxf2 Rf8 25. Nd2 Rxf2 26. Kh1
{ It is still far from clear despite the engines screaming '+3!' but of course White is great. Our plan is to use the h-Pawn - we should advance it as far as possible. }
