{ Black can't take  17...cxd5  as  18.Rg3  Kh7  19.e5!  dxe5  20.Rxe5  would win. }
17... Re8 18. a5
{ This is my improvement over Huschenbeth, N - Godena, M - Mitropa Cup 2018. White's point is that  18...cxd5  19.Rg3  is fine whereas if he retreats the Bishop to a7 then we can play 19. Rg3 and get an upgraded version of the same line. For practical reasons I prefer this over 18. Rg3 - it is less to remember. }
18... Ba7
{ As I said - we now get an upgraded version of Huschenbeth - Godena. } 19. Rg3
Kf8 20. Bh6+ Ke7 21. Bxf7 Rh8
{ Exactly as in the source game.  21...Kxf7  22.Rg7+  is too easy.   After  21...Rf8  22.Ba2  White is winning too as 23. e5 can't be stopped. }
22. e5 { Let's see how this is different from Huschenbeth-Godena. } 22... dxe5
{ In the game @@StartBracket@@without a5 Ba7, naturally@@EndBracket@@ Black played:   22...Rxh6??  and after  23.exf6+  Kxf7  24.Qg4  White was totally winning although  24.Rg7+  Kf8  25.Rg8+!  would be even simpler. }
23. Rxe5+ Kd7 24. Be6+ Kc7 25. Bf4 {  } 25... Nxe6 26. Rxe6+ Kc8 27. Rd3
{ White is completely winning. After  27...Qf8  28.Rxf6!  Qxf6  29.Qg4+  is the simplest. }
