34. Bd4 { Black has two possibilities now. } 34... Qd3
{ Black should be safe in the endgame. We should be safe too but we have to play actively. }
35. Qxd3+ Rxd3 36. Bf6 Rxd5 37. h4
{ White's plan is to advance the h-pawn and forget about the rest. } 37... Rd2+
38. Kf3 Rd3+ 39. Kg2 Rxa3 40. Nf4
{ It is important to see the line till the end as the drawing idea is very simple - once you see it. }
40... c5 41. h5 a5 42. Nh3
{ It's not the only move but it's the simplest way to secure the draw. } 42...
Kg8 43. Ng5 Ra2+ 44. Kg3 Ra3+ 45. Kh4 Ra2
{ We have no way of achieving 46.h5-h6, pity. } 46. Kg3 *

