34... Rb1 { 35.Bg5?  now fails to  35...Qe1  . } 35. Bg5
{ I want you to see this line so you could understand why we should go  35.a4  instead. }
35... Qe1 36. Qxe1 Rxe1 37. Bh6 Rh1 { 37... Re2 would also work. } 38. h3 Ra1
39. Nh5 Rxa3 40. Bxg7+ Kg8
{ Our King is trapped on h4 and it's going to take while before we can move it. Black Rook's Pawn is giving Black some practical chances to fight for more than just a draw. }
