12... Ra8
{ Compared with the 11...O-O move-order, White has now an extra option:  13.dxe5  Nxe5  14.Nxe5  dxe5  15.Qxd8+  Kxd8  16.Bxa7  Rxa7  17.Bxf7  looks fairly promising. However I wasn't satisfied with  17...Ke7!  18.Bb3  Rd8  and despite being a Pawn up it is not easy for White to make a progress. Therefore I would just allow transposition. }
