{ Swiercz thought this was a mistake but it seems that he was wrong about this one. However, it doesn't change my attitude - we should go for it as the lines aren't easy for Black. In this position White has two main tries: 13. Re1 and 13. d5.   13. Re1 scores well but I do expect this trend to change as it is quite easy to improve Black. My initial intention was to go for the most principal variation -   13. d5 I was aware that Black could equalize in that line but it was still quite challenging so though you wouldn't mind. Then, the game Grischuk - Giri happened @@StartBracket@@Zagreb 2021@@EndBracket@@ and at this point it was no longer challenging anymore - it was just a common knowledge. I had to come up with something new. }
