{ Black is preparing  17...Ne7  but something is wrong with this move, isn't it? Our radar immediately points to f7, the question is - how can we use it? }
17. Ng5 { The start is simple. } 17... d5 18. Qd1
{ Threatening 19. Qh5 or 19. Qf3 so 18...g6 is not good enough. } 18... Rxe3
{ Giving away the Queen for three pieces sounds tempting at first. } 19. Qh5
Qxg5 20. Qxg5 Rxb3
{ But for Black the problem is that his pieces lack coordination. } 21. Qxd5
Rxb2 22. Qd7 { Everything is based on tempo. } 22... h6 23. Re8+
{ Now the black minor pieces will be left without a defender. } 23... Rxe8 24.
Qxe8+ Kh7 25. Qe4+ Kg8 26. d5
{ I am not sure, maybe there is a lucky fortress but maybe not. Both  26...Nxa5  and Nb4 are met with  27.Qe5  while after  26...Nd4  we should simply win the Pawn on f7 with  27.Qe8+  . }
