14. Qe2
{ Compared with 13...h6 14. Qd2 some extra lines are possible which we should be aware of. }
14... exd4 15. cxd4 Bb7
{ Quite a provocative reaction as Black is basically inviting us to play  16.Ng5  . }
16. Ng5 { Invitation accepted. } 16... Re7 17. Ndf3
{ Black doesn't really have a choice now. The next few moves are pretty much forced. }
17... h6 18. Nxf7 Rxf7 19. Bxf7+ Kxf7 20. d5 Ne5
{ 20...Ne7  21.Bxa7  Rxa7  22.Rac1  would be also pleasant. } 21. Nxe5+ dxe5
22. Bxa7 Rxa7 23. Rac1
{ Black has two pieces for a Rook and a Pawn which normally is a good deal. Here however White has an advantage - Black pieces lack coordination and his position is full of weaknesses. Our plan is to double the Rooks on the c file. Black has to defend passively. }
