16... Bxd2 17. Qxd2 { 17.Nxd2!?  followed by 18. f4 is also interesting. }
17... Qxf6 18. Bd5
{ The Bishop is really dominant on d5! Our follow-up involves a typical maneuver: Nf3-h2-g4-e3. }
