14... c5 { One of the moves we should always consider first. } 15. dxc5 dxc5
16. Nc3
{ Taking the Pawn didn't offer much -  16.Bxc5  Bxc5  17.Qxc5  Nxe4  18.Qe5  Bb7  and Black is doing okay. It doesn't feel very secure, especially for our light-square Bishop but - for now - the c5 Pawn is pinned. }
16... Qc7 { Making c5-c4 a real threat. } 17. Qd2
{ It is nice to free up the c2 square for the Bishop but Be3-f4 would be even nicer. }
17... Ng6 { Covering f4 square. } 18. e5
{ The Pawn can't be taken as there's Be3-f4 at the end. } 18... Rd8 19. Qe2
{ 19...Nxe5??  fails again this time directly to  20.Bf4! } 19... c4
{ The only move. } 20. exf6 cxb3 21. Rfc1
{ It's not easy for Black to catch a breath. We didn't want to use the Queen's Rook - it should defend the Pawn on a5. This is not a pleasant choice for Black who doesn't seem to have a safe spot for the Queen.   21...Bxe3  should be answered with  22.fxe3!  gaining control over important central squares. }
