17... Qe8
{ It was a good move against  17.Rfd1  but now this is the worst possible choice for Black. The key difference is that the other Rook can now move to e1 creating a nice x-ray on the e file. However there is a more dynamic way of executing this idea: }
18. Bg5 { Creating an imminent threat of Bg5xf6. } 18... Nxe4
{ Black has to try this even though it is winning for White. } 19. Nxe4 Bxe4
{ 19...Qxe4  would be even worse -  20.Rfe1  and every Queen retreat loses on spot:  20...Qc6  21.Be7+-  ;   19...Qxe4  20...Qg6  21.Ne5+-  ;   19...Qxe4  20...Qf5  21.Re5!  Qg6  22.Nh4+-  . }
20. Rfe1 { Can Black save the Bishop? } 20... Kh8
{ He can defend it with f7-f5. However the light-squared Bishop is not the only problem for Black - his whole position is a drama - there is no coordination between the pieces, this house must fall. }
21. Bf4 Rc8 22. Bd6
{ Since  22...Rg8  is met with  23.Ng5  Black might as well resign. } *

