10. cxb3 d5 { Striking in the center looks most logical. } 11. Nxe5 dxe4 12.
Nc3
{ White calmly develops his pieces. There is no need to take on a6 yet as the a6 Pawn is pinned. It seems that Black is missing a tempo to get a real compensation. }
12... Bb7 13. bxa6 { Now is the time... } 13... Rxa6 14. Rxa6 Bxa6 15. d4
{ 15.Nc6  was also possible but the opposite-color Bishops mean good drawing odds. }
15... Bb7 { Black could not play  15...exd3??  due to  16.Nc6  . } 16. Bg5 h6
17. Bh4
{ We should play h2-h3 if given a chance and then see how Black develops as this is his main problem - developing his major pieces. }
