9. axb5 axb5 10. c3 d5
{ This version of Marshall is an upgrade for White who controls the a file. }
11. exd5 Nxd5 12. Nxe5 Nxe5 13. Rxe5 c6
{ It should just be a worse version of Marshall Gambit as White controls the a file. However it turns out that things aren't that simple. }
14. Re1 { Immediate  14.d3  would give Black an extra option:  14...b4!? }
14... Bd6
{ 14...b4?!  would now be answered with  14.c4  Nf4  15.d4  with a big advantage. }
15. d3
{ I prefer this over  15.d4  . White will enjoy a small edge while avoiding the complications. }
15... Qh4
{ White's last move was aimed especially against this response. Let's see why. }
16. g3 Qh3 17. Re4
{ With the pawn on d4 Black could now play  17...g5!  and White can't take the Pawn  17.Bxg5  because of  17...Qf5  with a fork. But now our Rook on e4 is defended. }
