{ A logical reaction turns out to be insufficient for equality: } 16. Ng3
{ It is really hard to recommend something for Black. } 16... g6
{ It doesn't look nice but it does do the job stopping Ng3-f5. Nyback played  16...cxd3  but after  17.Qxd3  White had a clear advantage. }
17. d4 exd4
{ At least Black is trying to get his own game. Otherwise this would be a one way traffic. }
18. cxd4 d5 19. e5 Ne4
{ Black has gained some nice points but it doesn't fully compensate the position of his King. }
20. Bh6 Re8 21. Qc1
{ in this complex position white retains better chances. The Queen will soon come to f4 creating fresh threats involving the Knight moves: Nxe4 and Ng5, Nh2-g4, Nf5 or Nh5. }
