{ Black should definitely call our bluff even though the following lines might look scary for him. }
17. Bxd6
{ 17.Nxd6  looked promising to me but the problem is that after  17...cxd6  18.Bxd6  Nxb3  19.Bxf8  Qxf8  20.Rxe4  Nc5  21.Rxb4  Black has  21...Nd3!  winning the Pawn on b2. What luck! }
17... cxd6 18. Nxd6
{ Literally everything is hanging but once again Black escapes with some tricks: }
18... Nxb3 19. Nxe4 Nd4 20. c3
{ Even now White is close to winning the Pawn but not close enough... } 20...
bxc3 21. bxc3 g6
{ Useful intermezzo. The Queen has to leave this nice square. } 22. Qc5 Rc8
{ And one more intermezzo although already now  22...Bg7  would be sufficient as well. }
23. Nxf6+ { There is no point in looking for advantage any more. } 23... Qxf6
24. Qxd4 Qxd4 25. Rxd4 { or  25.cxd4  Rc4=  . } *

