{ Black's problem is that he has no time for  15...Nd7  because of  16.Qb3+  and White wins the Pawn on b4. }
15... Kh8 16. Bxf6 Bxf6 17. Nd2
{ White is enjoying a typical good Knight vs bad Bishop edge. } 17... Bg5 18.
Nc4
{ For both sides it is not easy to find a good follow-up but White's position is easier. We can put the Rook on d1 and try some Queen moves like Qh3-h5. At some point we can allow Black to swap the Bishop for the Knight - anyway it will be pleasant as Black has some weaknesses on the queenside. }
