15. Bb1 { Trying to keep the Bishop, or at least trade it for its equivalent. }
15... c5
{ Black is happy to open up the position as his pieces are very active. } 16.
Nxe4 dxe4 17. Bxe4 Bxe4 18. Rxe4 c4
{ Black has a nice compensation for the Pawn. He controls many light squares and can improve his position quite easily which makes it a good practical try. I was lucky to execute this idea @@StartBracket@@and also win the game@@EndBracket@@ in my very first attempt in the 9...Rb8 line - Fedorchuk, S - Gajewski, G - European Championship 2005. }
