19. Nf1 g5 { It might seem attractive but White has a strong response. } 20.
Bd2 { Getting ready for Black's dark-squared Bishop. } 20... Bg7 21. Bc3 Ne5
{ Black is trying to set up a blockade. } 22. Nxe5 Bxe5 23. Nd2
{ It is becoming clear that Black is in trouble. Black has occupied e5 and built a dam on it but it is about to get broken.   Once the Knight comes to f3, the Bishops will get swapped and Black's position will become critical. Notice that, even though achieving e4-e5 might be tricky, as the Pawn on d5 needs protection, White has other plans that might be just as dangerous!   For instance, White can bring the Knight to d4, taking advantage of the opponent's Knight's unstable position. }
