19. Nf1 Qf6 20. Kg2
{ While many of us might be wondering if White's last move made much sense, it is clear that the King is better placed on g2 - it protects f3 and h3 which improves the coordination of White's pieces. White wants to play Bc1-d2 which will lead to significant changes in the character of the position. Before making such big decisions it is good to improve the position to the maximum. }
20... g5
{ It's easy to miss this detail but Black could not play  20...c4  because of  21.Qd2!  attacking the Knight and a Pawn. }
21. Bd2 Qxb2
{ Otherwise White would just play @@StartFEN@@r3rbk1/1b1n4/p2p1q1p/1ppP2p1/Pn2PpP1/R4N1P/1P1B1PK1/1B1QRN2 w - - 1 22@@EndFEN@@  21...--  22.Bc3  . }
22. Rb3 Qf6 23. axb5 axb5 24. Bxb4 cxb4 25. Rxb4
{ Black has chances to defend thanks to the nice control over the dark squares but still - White's position has a lot of potential! The Knights can be regrouped to f3 and c6/f5/e6, the e1-Rook can move to the c-file. Overall there is a lot of life in the position. }
