{ Now it is clear why the Knight would be better on e5, but also the normal  20.Re3  would be strong - compared to 18...Ne5, Black's Pawn on c4 is not defended. }
20... Qf6
{ Black's Queen is attacking the Knight and the Pawn on f2 but we can protect against both threats. }
21. Nf5 Nxe1
{ 21...axb5  would lead to the same position after  22.Rxa8  Bxa8  23.bxc5  Nxe1  . }
22. bxc5 axb5 { There was nothing else. } 23. Rxa8 Bxa8
{ White can't take the Knight due to Qf6xf5! but it's not a problem, we know what to do... }
24. c6 { Now the black bishop is doomed. } 24... g6
{ He'd better do this first - after the immediate  25...Nd3  26.Bxd3  cxd3  27.Qb3!  , 28.Bb2 is coming. }
25. Ne3 Nd3 26. Bxd3 cxd3 27. Nb3
{ Black won't be able to save the d3-Pawn and despite the material advantage, it is clear that Black is fighting for equality. }
27... Qc3 28. Bd2 Qb2 29. Ba5
{ The Pawn on d3 is falling. If Black tries  29...Qe2  then we can just go  30.Qxe2  dxe2  31.f3!  and the King will capture the Pawn, no worries. }
