20... Nbd3 { These knights cannot be tolerated for long. } 21. Bxd3 cxd3
{ This, in my opinion, is the best human reaction to our idea. Black has to find a couple of difficult moves but if he does that, he will be able to simplify the position. }
22. axb5 Nxe4 { The point of Black's previous move. } 23. b4
{ White is taking the c5-square away from the Knight. } 23... d2
{ The Pawn move is critical for Black as it disrupts the harmony of the white pieces. Instead,  23...Bxd5  24.Qxd3  axb5  25.Qxb5  would be better for White. }
