17. d5 Qc7
{ 17...c4  would be answered by  18.b4!  with total control over the queenside. White can start thinking about the other side... }
18. b3
{ Not the most pleasant position for Black as he doesn't have a good plan on the queenside -  18...c4  can be answered with both  19.b4  a5  20.a4!  and  19.bxc4!?   After the slower  18...a5  White can just clear the situation out with  19.c4  b4  20.a3  and soon White's attention will move to the kingside. }
