16... d5
{ A firm reaction but Black will now have to be accurate all the way to the end. }
17. Bg5 { White is increasing the pressure in the center. } 17... Qc8
{ This is by far the main move. The black Queen is simply moving away from the pin. }
18. dxe5 Nxe5
{ So far no top player decided to go for it but of course, it is better to anticipate the possible improvements for the other side. }
19. Nxe5 Rxe5 20. f4
{ If Black retreats the Rook with  20...Re8  then  21.e5  will give White an overwhelming edge. }
20... Rxe4
{ By sacrificing an exchange for a Pawn, Black is able to release the pressure in the center. }
21. Nxe4 Nxe4 22. Bxe4
{ We do not have to do this right now but the Knight cannot be tolerated for too long anyway. }
22... dxe4 23. Be7
{ Improving the position of the Bishop right in front of our opponent's nose. }
23... Qe6 24. Bc5
{ We can now put the Queen to e3. My guess is that Black should be able to hold this but that's okay. He has a much smaller margin of error and this matters more. }
