28. Re3 Rd8 29. Ne5 { 29.Nd4  would be answered with  29...c5  . } 29... Qf5
30. Rxd3 Rxd3 31. Nxd3 Qf6 { Finally, the weakness on c3 tells on. } 32. Nc5
{ At least trying to maintain the material advantage. } 32... Nxc5 33. bxc5
{ White is still a Pawn up, however, Black shouldn't have problems with holding this position by focusing on the weak Pawns on the queenside. }
