{ We just need to find the right way to punish Black. } 14. Nxb6
{ Starting with  14.g4  would be inaccurate but the explanation is hilarious -  14...Bf7  15.Nxb6  axb6!  and after  16.Bb2  Black has  16...Ba2! }
14... cxb6 15. g4 Bf7 16. Bf8 Qb5
{ Trying to keep the Queen is not a good idea... } 17. c4 Qb2 18. Ba3
{ 18.Bxg7  Rg8  19.Bh6  O-O-O!  would actually be fine for Black. } 18... Qc3
19. Qe2 b5 { Black had to open a5-d8 diagonal for the Queen. } 20. Rfc1 Qa5 21.
cxb5
{ It is a good moment to forget about the Queen and look at the whole board - Black is just lost - his King is stuck in the center with no hope for evacuation. After  21...cxb5  we can just go  22.Qb2  preparing d3-d4. }
