Bd6
{ The Bishop protects the crucial Pawn but it becomes a passive piece in the meantime. }
11. Nc4 f6 12. Na5
{ 12.Ne3  Nf8  13.Nf5  Qd7  seemed to work well for Black in So - Topalov, Shamkir 2020, so let's try to improve. Black now has to decide whether he castles long or not. }
12... O-O-O
{ This was Black's intention all along. His setup is strong but we have a very interesting way to challenge it. }
13. Qe1
{ It is not amateur playing - after  13...Bxf3  White has  14.Qe3!  - nice trick! }
13... g5
{ Attack on the Kingside is one thing but Black also prevents Nf3-h4 with this. }
14. Nd2
{ The Knight is heading to c4 and perhaps to e3? White is a bit better here - once the Knight lands on c4 we can go Ra1-b1 preparing a3-a4. For Black it is not easy to create counterplay as g5-g4 is always answered with h3-h4. }
