14... f6 { Strengthening e5 but also making some room for the Bishop. } 15. a4
Kb8 16. Nc4
{ White has a very nice advantage - we have a better Pawn structure and Black has some weak light squares - something that we can use, especially in the endgame. We can go b4-b5 but also d3-d4 or just Nc4-e3.   The most natural follow-up is  16...Nb6  17.Nxd6  Qxd6  18.d4  . }
