{ White is trying the same idea, only without a2-a4 and a7-a5. Notice that it would be too late to try  13.a4  as Black can play  13...exd4  14.a5  Bc5  . }
13... Rfe8
{ 13...exd4  is also possible as after  14.Ba3  Black has  14...Bc5! } 14. Re1
{ White's Rook is supporting the Pawn on e4. } 14... exd4 15. Nxb6 axb6
{ With a2-a4 and a7-a5 included, Black would be forced to recapture with the c-Pawn or the Knight instead. Apart from the general rule @@StartBracket@@capturing with the Pawn to the center is stronger@@EndBracket@@ 15...axb6 is much stronger for a couple of reasons:  Black gets counterplay on the a-file; the d6-square is now covered by the Pawn on c7; Black is more likely to achieve c6-c5 in a good version. }
