17. Rfe1
{ The best try. The Pawn on e4 is more important than its colleague on d4 - it controls the d5-square. }
17... Rxd4 18. Bxa5
{ Black can now choose between collecting the Pawn on a4 and e4. Which one should he choose? }
18... Rxa4
{ Black is correct not to be afraid of  19.Bxb6  Rxa1  20.Rxa1  cxb6  21.Ra8+  Kc7  . However, White has something stronger: }
19. Qg4+ { Now g7 will fall. } 19... Qe6 20. Qxg7 Qg6
{ This is the only way to prevent Black's position from collapse. } 21. Qxg6
hxg6 { 21...fxg6  22.Bc3  would be similar. } 22. f3
{ White is better as his Pawns on the kingside are far more dangerous. We can start advancing them with g2-g4 and h3-h4. The Bishop belongs to c3. }
