9. h3 Bxf3
{ Black is giving away his Bishop pair and it makes sense as his pieces were slightly crowded. }
10. Nxf3
{ 10.Qxf3  , chosen by Kravtsiv is also possible. For Black, the problem is that he can't easily improve the position of the Knight, which, usually in these structures, is why he starts with @@StartBracket@@Nd7-f8-e6@@EndBracket@@. }
10... O-O 11. d4
{ It's a direct approach - White is getting a nice Pawn center. Those who prefer keeping the position closed might consider  11.Nh4!?  , which is also interesting. }
11... exd4 12. cxd4 Bb6 13. a4
{ As you can see a2-a4 is quite typical in these structures, once again it is useful that the Rook controls a3. }
13... a5 14. b3 Rfe8 15. Re1 Rad8 16. Bb2
{ White has a nice position thanks to his Pawn center. We can finish our development with Qd1-c2 and Ra1-d1. }
