{ This natural move was played in Firouzja - Le Quang, once again in the World Blitz Championship in Moscow 2019. We have no way of finding out whether this was the Vietnamese player's oversight or rather a home cooking as Firouzja didn't choose the most critical response - it was a blitz game after all. }
9. d4 { Taking advantage of the placement of Black's pieces. } 9... g5 10. dxe5
gxh4
{ This is stronger than  10...Bxe5  11.Nxe5  gxh4  12.Qxd8+  Rxd8  13.Nc3  with advantage. }
11. exd6 cxd6 12. Nc3 Nh5 13. Qd4
{ Our line is not only strong but also practical as it is limiting Black's possibilities. }
13... Rg8 14. Kh1
{ Black's hopes on the g-file were more than obvious. He has to deal with his weaknesses - the h-Pawns are weak but also the d6-Pawn needs attention. }
14... h3 { 14...Bg4  would be simply met by  15.Ne1  . } 15. g3 Qf6
{ Black is lucky to have this double attack as it allows him to solve his development problems. However the long-term problems remain. }
16. Qxf6 Nxf6 17. Nd4
{ White is preparing f2-f3 which would give him quite a lot of benefits as it:   1. strengthens the position of White's central Pawn;   2. takes away from Black the g4-square;   3. enables the white King's march to the center via g1-f2-e3. }
17... O-O-O 18. f3
{ The setup is complete. We now have many improving moves such as Ra1-e1, Kh1-g1-f2 or regrouping the white Knight from c3 to e3 or f2. }
18... d5
{ Black didn't have the same comfort and playing in the center was basically his only plan. It doesn't look nice but at least he can hope for some counterplay. }
19. e5 Nd7 20. Rae1
{ White has a small edge thanks to his superior Pawn structure. We would like to improve the position of our c3 Knight - the f4-square looks nice, but how to get there without sacrificing the Pawn on e5? Let's first bring the King to f2 before making further decisions.   Also please note that White should be careful with f3-f4 - it creates a perfect Pawn chain but on the other hand, it's losing control over the g4-square. Black can put the Bishop on g4, the Pawn on h5 and it might be very difficult for White to make any progress. }
