10... Bh5 11. Nbd2 Nd7
{ 11...Qe7  would be answered exactly the same:  12.d4! } 12. d4 exd4
{ This is too soft, White should be slightly better now. Notice that it is practically a rule in the 6...Bd6 line - taking on d4 is almost never a good choice. I think it's mainly caused by the fact that Black actually prefers his Pawn on c7 rather than d6. }
13. Bxd6 cxd6 14. Nc4
{ Black can go  14...Qf6  or  14...Ne5  or just  14...O-O  - it doesn't really matter as we react in the same way -  15.Qxd4  .   Naturally  14...c5  forces us to take the other one:  15.Nxd6+  Kf8  16.Nf5  . In all cases White has a pleasant position. }
