{ A few years back we would call this plan 'unusual' but not anymore. White is preparing c3-d4. }
7... O-O 8. d4 Bd6 { The center is ours but Black's position remains solid. }
9. Bg5
{ Black now has to decide whether he will go f7-f6 or try to avoid it. Our Bishop will end up on g3 regardless. }
9... Be7
{ This is a solid move on one hand but on another White can get a pleasant position without much of an effort. }
10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. Qc2
{ In Naiditsch - Zhou, Chinese League 2011,  11.Nbd2  was played and Black continued with  11...exd4  . The point was that if White recaptures  12.cxd4  then Black goes  12...Rd8  followed by 13...Nf8 - we would prefer our Knight on c3 in this case. Hence we want to wait a little bit before developing the Knight. }
11... Rd8 12. h3
{ Now Black has to decide - he can either take on d4 or make a waiting move as well. If Black decides to go something like  12...a5  or  12...f6  then we can respond with  13.Nbd2  - it is always a small victory. }
