9. Re1 { Not the best square for the Rook but we need to defend our own. } 9...
Bg7 10. c4 O-O 11. Nc3 Nh5
{ I don't like this move as the Knight has no perspective on h5 but it is the most popular in the position... }
12. Be3 h6 { He has to prevent Nf3-g5 before going f7-f5. } 13. a4
{ Once again we don't mind  13...a5  14.c5  . } 13... f5 14. exf5 Nxf5 15. a5
{ White has full control in the center as the e4-square is ours. At the same time, we have a free hand on the Queenside - we should now make sure of our control over e4.   We can play h2-h3 and then if the Black Knight comes back to f6, we can try g4!? getting control over f5 too. Once we have full control in the center we can then start playing on the Queenside. }
