{ There was no reason to play  14.h3  . Compared with the normal Chigorin Variation,  the Knight is already on g3 which makes all the cxd4/cxd4 lines easier for White who doesn't have a problem with finding a place for the light-squared Bishop. }
14... exd4 15. cxd4 cxd4
{ The most solid line for Black but also a sad one... } 16. Nxd4 Bb7 17. b3
{ Taking away the c4-square from the Black's Knight but also making some room for the Bishop. }
17... Rc8 18. Bb2 Nc6 { The Knight was useless on a5. } 19. Nxc6 Bxc6 20. Qd2
{ This is a small improvement over Tari-Svidler, Chess24 October Blitz 2020 where  20.Qd4  was played.  Black wants to play d7-d5 and open up the position even at the cost of a Pawn. We are going to try to keep some more tension on board. }
20... d5 21. e5 Ne4 22. Qe2
{ This is the point. We are now threatening to win a Pawn but without exchanging the Queens. }
22... Qb6 { Solid and human reaction. } 23. Nxe4 dxe4 24. Bxe4 Bxe4 25. Qxe4
{ Black has some compensation for the Pawn but definitely not enough so he has to fight for a draw. We can place the Rook on d1 and don't forget about h2-h3! }
