{ What I like about this move is that it forces Black to react but it's not clear how he should deal with it. }
12... Rb8
{ In my opinion, this is the best reaction although it doesn't look too encouraging for Black who has just given up on the a-file. }
13. axb5 axb5 14. Nb3 { From here the Knight controls d4, c5 and... a5! } 14...
Nb6
{ 14...dxc3  15.bxc3  b4  16.Bb2  would still be better for White as Black would be left with a permanent weakness on c6. }
15. Na5 { Eliminating the defender and also making room for the Bishop. } 15...
Nxa5 16. Rxa5 Nd7
{ The Knight has barely touched b6 and it already has to come back... } 17.
cxd4 c5 18. b4 cxd4 { 18...cxb4?  19.Ra2  would be clearly better for White. }
19. Bd2
{ It isn't much but it's definitely pleasant. We can put the Bishop on b3 and maybe move the Queen, perhaps to a2? The kingside Rook can occupy the c-file. }
