1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6
{ The Petroff Defence has always been one of the most solid lines out there but it has also had a reputation of boring. I think today it would be unfair to call it boring.   Sure, it is not the Najdorf Variation but still many lines are really sharp and dynamic. Hence, it should not surprise us that there are many strong and aggressive players, that use it as a part of their repertoire. }
3. Nxe5 d6 4. Nf3 Nxe4 5. d4
{ 5.Nc3  is another fashionable possibility but I wouldn't recommend it to everyone. The lines can often be quite difficult and computer-ish and - if I have a choice - I prefer something more natural. }
5... d5 6. Bd3 Be7 7. O-O Nc6 8. Nbd2
{ One of the changes in the modern theory - for years  8.c4  has been considered topical but in the last decade  8.Nbd2  came into play. White is basically saying that symmetrical structure doesn't mean equality. }
