Nf5
{ An old rule applies - the black Knights take each other's squares so they are not very effective, hence we should leave them as they are. }
18... Bf8
{ This was played by Jan-Krzysztof and it was the most natural continuation but somehow Black quickly got into trouble. }
19. h5 Qd7
{ One more natural continuation and Black cannot be saved.  19...Re4  had to be played but after  20.Rxe4  dxe4  21.N3h4  White is much better. Suddenly there is this deadly threat - Qb3-g3 and there is nothing Black can do. }
20. N3h4 Kh8
