{ A novelty. As I mentioned earlier, Humpy's 20...Kf8! solved Black's problems in the18.Bxd6 line so I want to try something else. }
18... g6 { Black is covering f5 and also enabling Kg8-f7. } 19. b3
{ Unless Black provokes h4-h5 with 19...Re4, we will continue with c2-c4. Black's position is solid but he is under pressure and we may potentially attack on both sides. }
