26. Bxe5+ Kg8
{ 26...Bf6  27.Rxf6  Rxf6  28.Bxf6+  Kg8  29.Qh5  would be easily winning. }
27. Qb3 { The point of 25.Rxe4! } 27... Rf7
{ If Black is not lost then he is winning so he'd better be lost. } 28. Rg6+
{ The Rook can't be taken -  28...hxg6  29.h7+  is mate in four. } 28... Kf8
{ Again, it doesn't look like White is winning -  29.Rg7  is easily refuted by  29...Qf5  . }
29. Bg7+ Kg8 30. Bf6+
{ Covering the f-file. Once again  30...hxg6  31.h7+  is a quick mate. } 30...
Kf8 31. Rg7 { But this is even quicker! Black can't prevent mate in two. } *

