{ 5.Nc3  is another fashionable possibility but I wouldn't recommend it to everyone. The lines can often be quite difficult and computer-ish and - if I have a choice - I prefer something more natural. }
5... d5 6. Bd3 Bd6
{ This is, no doubt, the most interesting line in 5.d4 Petroff, but it is also the least solid one. }
7. O-O O-O 8. c4
{ Undermining Black's position in the center. Other moves don't really matter. }
8... c6 { No other move deserved even an honorable mention. } 9. Nc3
{ In recent years it has become the most topical continuation in the 6...Bd6 variation. White immediately challenges the black Knight. }
