19... Bd5
{ By giving back a Pawn, Black is looking for a rescue in simplifications. }
20. Bxd5 cxd5 21. Rxd5 Nc6 22. Ba3
{ White has a big advantage - his pieces dominate on the board.  22...Rfd8  can be met with  23.Rad1  and we don't mind further simplifications as it will be much easier for our King to centralize. }
