12... O-O
{ Solid choice but not very impressive, throughout the whole line you might get an impression that Black's position is unpleasant, at least this is what I sense. }
13. Bf4 g5
{ It's a controversial decision but one of the few lines where Black ventures behind the 6th rank. :-@@EndBracket@@ }
14. Bd2 g4 { Otherwise he would only weaken the light squares for no reason. }
15. Ne5 Nxe5 16. dxe5 Qd7
{ Black's position is quite sound but so is ours. Besides, we are intending to attack his King, which makes positional factors less relevant, at least for now. }
17. h3
{ We are threatening 18.Qg3 @@StartBracket@@Black won't be able to take on h3 due to Bd2-h6@@EndBracket@@.   If Black now takes  17...gxh3  then we have  18.Re3!  followed by 19.Rxh3  and  19...hxg2?  20.Kxg2  is already winning for White as the other Rook joins the attack as well. }
17... Rae8
{ Black's point is that after  18.Qg3  he has a surprising  18...f5!  and nothing is clear. }
18. Bc3
{ 19.hxg4 is a threat so Black has to defend the d5-Pawn. After  18...c6  we have  19.Re4!  gxh3  20.Re3!  with initiative. }
