{ This is a sideline but it has a Giri trademark.  14.Bxg6  fxg6  15.Qc2  is main but with lots of games played already and Black appears to be quite solid. }
14... Bxd3
{ Black is correct not to wait any longer -  14...Rae8  15.Bxg6  fxg6  16.Qc2  is better for White. }
15. Qxd3 a6 { Preventing Qd3-b5. } 16. Rae1 Rae8
{ So far we were following Giri, A - Yu, Y from Tata Steel Masters 2020. It is time to deviate. }
17. h4
{ Giri went  17.Re2  but I think that doubling the Rooks is not that important. }
17... Bd8 18. h5
{ Black can't yet go  18...Rxe1  19.Rxe1  Re8??  because of  20.Qf5!  and White is winning. }
18... h6 19. Nd2
{ We want to go Nb3-c5. Once again  19...Rxe1  20.Rxe1  Re8  is not the best idea -  21.Rxe8+  Qxe8  22.Qf5  and after  22...Qe6  23.Qxe6  fxe6  24.Nb3  followed by Nc1-d3 White has a clear advantage in the endgame. }
