9. Nc7 d4 { Counterattacking in the center. } 10. Nxa8
{ 10.Ne2?!  g5!  would become messy. } 10... dxc3 11. Qxd8 Bxd8
{ This line is not dangerous but we react differently than after  11...Rxd8  which makes it important. }
12. b3 { After  12.bxc3?  Ba5!  things would become messy. } 12... Nbd7 13. f3
{ We will castle long on the next move. Black has no way of winning the Knight, in fact, he has no way of doing anything significant, White is just winning. While looking at the position I had a strong feeling that White owes everything to his supported Pawn on e4.   To confirm my observation I set up the same position without this Pawn. The evaluation dropped from 3.5 to -5. The value of the pieces really is relative. }
