11. Qd4
{ It is important to understand why  11.Qe3  wouldn't be as strong - you will find an explanation to that in the comments to  11...Nxc3  12.bxc3  Ba3+  13.Kb1  Na6  . }
11... Nxc3 { Black will try to use his Bishop pair. } 12. bxc3 Ba3+ 13. Kb1 Na6
{ This is just losing, yet it was the best move after 11.Qe3, so what is the difference? }
14. Bxa6 bxa6 15. Nxa8 Qa5 16. Ka1 Be6 17. Nc7
{ Looks simple, doesn't it? Now imagine what would happen if the white Queen is on e3 - there is d5-d4! }
