[Result "*"]

1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. Be3
{ The Classical System has never been doing better against the Pirc. Black seems to be struggling everywhere, while the main challenge for White is that it is quite easy to mix up some moves in the beginning.   With his last move, White develops the piece to a natural square. We can feel that the exciting long castle is coming, but what I like about this line is its flexibility - we can easily adapt to Black's plans so whenever it suits us, we can also castle short. }
4... Ng4
{ Mamedyarov likes to play this in blitz games occasionally. Otherwise, there is no value for Black here. }
5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 Bg7
{ We could now transpose to the @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/ppp1pp1p/3p1np1/8/3PP3/2N1B3/PPP2PPP/R2QKBNR b KQkq - 1 4@@EndFEN@@  4...Bg7  5.Qd2  Ng4  6.Bg5  h6  7.Bh4  line with @@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/ppp1ppb1/3p2pp/8/3PP1nB/2N5/PPP2PPP/R2QKBNR w KQkq - 2 7@@EndFEN@@  7.Qd2  but we have an even stronger move. }
7. Be2 { It's good that the Queen was still on d1. } 7... Nf6 8. Qd2
{ White is clearly better, we can go f2-f4 and start pressuring Black. } *

