23. b4 { Dragging Black's Queen to an inferior square. } 23... Qxb4
{ 23...Qh5  would quickly lose after  24.Rxe6  fxe6  25.Bxe6+  Rf7  26.Qf6  . }
24. Qf6 { Threatening both 25.Bh6 and 25.Rxe6. } 24... g5
{ 25.Bxg5??  would be answered with the simple  25...Qxd6  26.Bh6  Qe5-+  . }
25. Bd2
{ Now it is clear why we needed Black's Queen on b4 - if it was on a5, he would have now played Qa5-e5! }
25... Qxd6 26. Bc3
{ Black has to give away the whole Queen in order to escape from an imminent mate. }
