11. Rxa5
{ Considering Na5xb3 would be Black's next move, it's actually quite natural. }
11... Bxa5 12. dxe5
{ This reminds me of some old classical scenarios in the Ruy Lopez - instead of developing his pieces Black has gotten greedy and here comes the punishment... }
12... Ng4 13. Bg5
{ Simple and strong - White develops another piece with tempo. } 13... Qd7
{ 13...f6  14.exf6  gxf6  15.Bh4  was completely winning for White in Dolmatov - Sivokho, Chigorin Memorial 2000. }
14. e6 { Disconnecting Black's pieces. } 14... fxe6 15. Nd4 e5 16. Nf5
{ 16.Be6  Qxe6!  17.Nxe6  Bxe6  would still offer Black some chances for saving the game but after the text move, it should be over.  White is threatening 17.Qxg4 as well as 17. Be6 and there's no good defense to both of them. }
*

